sober /ˈsəʊbə/

1. ADJ When you are sober , you are not drunk. 清醒的 

例： He'd been drunk when I arrived. Now he was sober. 我到的时候他已经喝醉了。现在他清醒了。 

2. ADJ A sober person is serious and thoughtful. 严肃的 

例： We are now far more sober and realistic. 我们现在严肃多了，也现实多了。 

例： It was a room filled with sad, sober faces. 这是一个满是忧伤和严肃面孔的房间。 

3. soberly ADV 严肃地 

例： 'There's a new development,' he said soberly. “有新的进展，”他严肃地说。 

4. ADJ Sober colours and clothes are plain and rather dull. (颜色或衣服) 素淡的 

例： He dresses in sober grey suits. 他穿着一套素净的灰色衣服。 

5. soberly ADV 素淡地 [ADV with v] 

例： She saw Ellis, soberly dressed in a well-cut dark suit. 她看见了埃利斯，素淡地穿着一套裁剪合体的黑西服。 

6.  →  see also sobering

